## `<file-level: public API>`
<!-- checksum: rust-lib-1 -->

### Purpose
Library crate root. Declares all modules and re-exports the public surface. Replaces Python's `sqlite_fs/__init__.py`.

### Postconditions
- `cargo build` produces `libsqlite_fs.rlib` with every module.
- Users depend on `sqlite-fs = "0.1"` and write `use sqlite_fs::{mkfs, open_fs, Filesystem, ...}`.
- Private submodules not re-exported (callers must not reach into `nodes`, `entries`, `blobs`, `xattrs`, `symlinks`, `fdtable`, `locks`, `perms`, `schema`, `paths` — internal implementation).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
//! sqlite-fs — a durable, performant FUSE filesystem backed by SQLite (Rust port).

// Internal modules
mod blobs;
mod entries;
mod fdtable;
mod locks;
mod nodes;
mod paths;
mod perms;
mod schema;
mod symlinks;
mod xattrs;

// Public modules (their items get re-exported below)
pub mod errors;
pub mod types;
pub mod watch;
mod fs;
mod fsck;
mod mkfs;

#[cfg(feature = "fuse")]
pub mod fuse;

// Public API re-exports
pub use errors::{Error, Result};
pub use fs::Filesystem;
pub use mkfs::{mkfs, open_fs, MkfsOptions, OpenOptions};
pub use schema::{SyncMode, DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE};
pub use types::{
    Access, DirEntry, Event, EventKind, FsckIssue, FsckKind, FsckReport,
    IntegrityResult, LockOp, FlockOp, LockQuery, LockType, NodeKind, Stat,
};
pub use watch::Watcher;
```

### Failure Modes
None (declarations only).

### Test Strategy

```rust
// Compile-test: just depend on sqlite-fs; this file ensures re-exports are reachable.
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    #[test]
    fn public_symbols_reachable() {
        // Each use-statement is a compile-time check.
        use crate::{Error, Filesystem, MkfsOptions, OpenOptions, mkfs,
                    open_fs, SyncMode, Access, DirEntry, Stat, Watcher};
        let _ = std::any::TypeId::of::<Error>();
        let _ = SyncMode::default();   // plan.v7: Normal
    }
}
```

